-- Turkish Stock Exchange Changes to Top Stocks Effective Today
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-01-02T09:18:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/turkish-stock-exchange-changes-to-top-stocks-effective-today.html
Changes to the top 100 and top 30
stocks on the  Istanbul Stock Exchange , the most commonly traded
indexes of Turkish shares, went into effect today after being
announced on December 16.  Turcas Petrol AS (TRCAS) ,  Deva Holding AS (DEVA) ,  Rhea Girisim AS (RHEAG)  and
 Mutlu Aku & Malzemeleri Sanayi AS (MUTLU)  were added to the top 100,
while  Enka Insaat & Sanayi AS (ENKAI) ,  Turk Traktor & Ziraat Makineleri
AS (TTRAK)  and  Tofas Turk Otomobil Fabrikasi AS (TOASO)  were added to the top
30.  Zorlu Enerji Elektrik Uretim AS,  Turk Ekonomi Bankasi AS (TEBNK) ,
 OMV Petrol Ofisi AS (PTOFS)  and  Anel Elektrik Proje Taahhut & Ticaret AS (ANELE) 
were removed from the top 100, while  Koza Anadolu Metal
Madencilik Isletmeleri AS (KOZAA) ,  Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR)  and  Dogan
Yayin Holding AS (DYHOL)  were removed from the top 30.  The shares may move as theyâ€™re included or excluded from
the indexes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
